To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, we use the following formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Gross Profit = 2,329,939.23
- Total Revenue = 5,064,939.23

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{2,329,939.23}{5,064,939.23} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 0.4600 \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 46.00\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '46.00%'} }
```
